column6: Great fit and all day comfort. Just the right amount of shiny so that you feel like you have stylish leggings on but not so much that it’s overdone. Love how the high waisted leggings stay put during mat workouts!

These leggings are SO comfortable. I am a big fan of the Wunder Under collection and these are just as comfortable & stretchy but super cute with the metallic foil. The fabric is more "slippery" to the touch - no issue with lint or hairs on these leggings. The only issue I have with this pair is that there is a very noticeable black seem going right down the front and center (which can be unflattering on ladies... if you know what I mean). I can't speak to longevity yet, I've worn them a few times around town and haven't washed them, but so far so good! I got the same size as all Lululemon - size 6, 5'4, 135lb.
Super cute and fun workout pant! Can be worn to the gym or out and about to run errands. Very high waisted and flattering on the legs and booty.

I've always been a huge fan of wunder unders. I wasn't sure how these foil ones would look in person, but they are GORGEOUS! They function during a workout just as any other wunder under pair would, but they look so cute I'm considering wearing them out as cute leggings instead. The shine is flattering without calling attention to flaws. Highly recommend!

So disappointed in these. I own many pairs of lululemon pants and usually love them so SO much, but these didn’t live up to the lulu standards. The fit is nice but the color and quality after washing is a major let down. The foil print is not as shiny as in the picture, it’s more of a dull gray. After washing one time the print has basically washed away. And I am very careful with washing and hang drying my lulus since they are so expensive. I bought these specifically for the fun color since I already have so many black and gray lulus but now these look like the rest of them :( also, the high rise fit doesn’t go up as high as my other “high rise” lulus.

column6:
As Ja Rule once said "I too was hustled, scammed, bamboozled, hood winked, lead astray"
Let me just start by saying I own many lululemon pieces and I've been extremely happy with every purchase I've made.. until these bad boys came in the mail. These leggings do not resemble the photo above they don't have that "foil" shine it's more like a speckled gray? It sort of just makes the leggings look dirty lol. I decided to still give these leggings a shot and like most Luxtreme fabric bottoms they did their job performance wise. Now here's the major issue, after ONE wash the "foil" specks began to fall off. I take very good care of my leggings- I never put them in the drier, so I know this wasn't the case.
Bottom line my leggings now look like a dirty composition notebook. I don't know lulu, you kind of broke my heart with this one.

column6: The print is cute, I was hoping the material would be a little thicker like all of my other lulu leggings but they aren't. Not worth $80.
Nice fabric and color. I like it.

These leggings are just perfect. I was a little nervous about the material, but after wearing to the gym they broke in like a charm. No issues will pulling up, waistband issues, or feel like they were going to stretch too much. The color is also so much fun and can be worn for date night.
Live those tights! They fit wonderfully and so versatile, I can wear it to the gym and for a night out- très chic!

These pants are gorgeous, so pretty in fact I think I’ll save them for going out and not actually working out. I almost feel like they even make me look a little slimmer. I cannot attest to the longevity of the foil look of the pants but I hope these hold up to washing because these are my new favorites
My favorite leggings in flashy color. I got so many stares :)

I’ve tried many other top brands (you know them) in this style of faux leather, shimmer, etc leggings and these are by far the best!! They are hugging, tight in all the right places without being too tight. They hide all the stuff you want hidden and look super sexy. I wear working out but more for going out. Love these!! I am 5’10” and these are long enough for me.
I ordered these a size up, and they fit pretty well. I washed them too, the foil is still in tact.
column15: i wish these had side pockets.

column6: These pants are better than I expected! They fit really well and the foil look is eye-catching.
I like these tights but I read they didn't hold up with washing. So I returned because I want confident they would hold up
These pants are amazing. So flattering and can be dressed up or down. Most of my wardrobe is Lululemon, and these are my favorite pair of pants!
I bought these pants to wear under tunic style tops. They have a shiny texture that dresses up an outfit slightly more than solid black leggings. They look amazing!
I usually buy the align or movement tights. Because they stay put and I love them! Not these ones. I love how they look. But I kept having to re-adjust and pull the waistband up during class.

column6: I feel like a Rockstar when I wear these. They don't have has much stretch as most of my leggings, but they fit great!
Same great fit and feel of the normal Luxtreme Wunder Under pants but w a sexy, shimmery foil finish. I love these so much. Wear my normal size 8. 5’9” athletic build. Get these. You won’t regret it.

column6: I bought these leggings in both colors and totally loving them. They’re really stylish, very trendy, yet they are very functional, which is a necessity because I work out hard. I read other reviews about them not washing well so I was a bit worried. I have been turning them inside out and washing them on delicate and they’ve held up well so far. I don’t even know if this is necessary, but I love them so much — trying to be overly careful, just in case! Would LOVE to see these leggings in a dark blue, hunter green or deep, dark red. Please make more of these leggings! Love them!!!!

column5: Love the design, but the sheen wears off
column6:
I have only worn and washed these leggings twice but already the sheen has faded. They look like regular black leggings now! I washed them inside-out in cold water and line dried them. It's hugely disappointing as they looked so nice brand new, I bought a matching Energy Bra and Define Jacket in black foil too.
A side note in general about LLL's leggings -- I noticed over the last 6-12 months they changed their cut so that the leggings are roomier in the calves for regular-height people. As someone who is 5'1" 105 lbs (size 4 pants), LLL's leggings are baggy around the calves to the ankles for me, so not as good a fit as before. These pants are no exception -- very baggy around the calves and ankles even after hemming.

column6: I was so looking forward to getting these leggings. I love the Wunder Under, wear them religiously and sadly, these are a disappointment. The fit and cut of the fabric was not the same at all. Thankfully, Lululemon is great with returns.
column11: I KEEP MY AGE ON THE D.L.

column6: The fit and fabric are unlike any other. They look great, are super flattering, and feel great on!

column5: Just the right amount of sparkle!
column6: These are going to be dual-purpose for me. I'll certainly use them for yoga, probably mostly for special classes where I'm comfortable standing out a bit, but I'll also use them with outfits that can use a little dressing up. The black is nice and dark with just a bit of sparkle, not a lot. I'm wearing them during the day with a Santa shirt that has a tiny patch (Santa's wearing a hat) of black sparkle. And during the evening with a nice sweater and boots. I sized down in these, just as I did in the Luna this past summer.
column11: I KEEP MY AGE ON THE D.L.

column5: Cute but stretch out and fall
column6: I loved them when I first wore them. They fit like a glove and have a subtle shine that's easy to rock in an every day setting & dress up. But after wearing for a couple hours the waistband stretched out like crazy, causing the leggings to slip down. The quality is definitely not worth the price, I wish I just got another pair of normal wonder unders.

column6: As the proud owner of over 300 pairs of wunder unders I am going to rank these in the top 10 of my collection. The shine is gorgeous, and the fit even better! A classic for any age, and shape. LOVE!

Was obsessed with these pants when I first bought them - I loved the sheen! However after one wash & line dry (1), the sheen is gone. Would not have purchased these knowing that the sheen didn't hold - should have read these reviews! Total bummer.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Dear ssspenceee,\n\nThank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us. We're so sorry to hear that your Wunder Under Hi Rise Tight Foil is not performing for you. Keep an eye out for an email coming your way. Chat soon!", 'LL_response_date': 'December 14, 2018'}

column6: Very comfortable and great for working out!! They fit like a glove:)

column5: Love the design... not the fit
column6: I really liked the design of these pants, I was excited to switch things up!!!! I was disappointed with the waist band because it had seam at the very top that cut into my sides and made it look very unflattering. I loved the design and the fit throughout the legs, but I’ll unfortunately have to return because of the waist band.

These fit like a leather glove, tight in all the right places! Unfortunately, they don't wear like a leather glove... These pants are gorgeous. The sheen is subtle, just perfect. They were difficult to put on compared to my other 2's (I wear size 2). But once I got them on, they were amazing. So comfortable!
Wait, oh no {crying}... after washing them the sheen is non existent. I always expect the best from LuluLemon, especially for the price. They must've forgotten to test these in the washing machine. They look just like my black mat pair of leggings now. Unacceptable.

column6: Initially, I loved these pants. They look great on, the foil print is fun, and they work well for me in both hot and flow yoga equally well. However, after a few wears, the foil is starting to wear off areas of impact. For the type of yoga I do, that's in the knee and butt area. If you're getting these to just wear around - go for it! But for those who use their lulus to practice, it's worth being aware of the functional wear in this print.

column6: I thought these would be so cute when I bought them in store. When I tried them on, I was overwhelmed with a synthetic smell of sorts. I decided to get them and try washing them... However, when I washed them, the shiny/glittery aspect almost completely went away, and they still smell super synthetic, rubbery, chemically - Something. It got to the point it gave me a headache each time I tried wearing them.

column5: Run small not very sparkly once on
column6:
I ordered my regular sz 6 and I could barely get these over my calves (they are not large at all) Once I managed to get them on, waist hips felt OK but the sparkle was gone, they still had a slight shimmer to these not at all like they look on the model in the picture. I'm worried if I go with a size up, as I wear them they will start to feel to big.
Fabric felt really, really thin for luxtreme. Really disappointed, these will sadly be going back

Honestly these pants are absolutely amazing when you first get them. I would give a 5 plus rating. Then after about 4 washes in the directions they give you they sparkly foil came off. I'm left with tights that look almost just plain black. If they weren't such a great look and great fit I would have given a 1. But they are great other then the sparkle foil came off.
